Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?feat(gbrain):=20TriDBEngine=20=E2=80=94=20run?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20gBrain=20on=20TriDB=20(native=20graph=20leg)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A third BrainEngine backend (engine: 'tridb') that extends PostgresEngine. TriDB
is PG 13.4 + pgvector (the -pgv image) + the native graph_store_am AM. Vector leg
(pgvector cosine/hnsw), BM25, pages/facts/takes, migrations all inherit unchanged;
only the GRAPH leg is native:
- initSchema: + CREATE EXTENSION graph_store_am + register link types
- syncGraphFromLinks: one-pass populate the native AM from the relational links
  table (identical topology for the head-to-head benchmark)
- traverseNative: early-terminating native BFS (vs the inherited recursive-CTE
  traverseGraph) — the +31 P@5 graph leg, measured honestly
- addLink/removeLink: dual-write (relational metadata + native topology, one WAL)
Typechecks clean (bun x tsc --noEmit, 0 errors). First-cut: full traverseGraph/
traversePaths GraphNode-rebuild overrides are a follow-on.
